{"TopicId":130384,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"[STOCK] Klermont - Stock Paddleboat","CreatedByName":"Bubbadevlin","CreatedById":136524,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-21T03:11:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Bubbadevlin","CreatedById":136524,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-21T03:11:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003EBubbadevlin Presents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003EThe Klermont\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uB6Pcgr.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/uB6Pcgr.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:36px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz8Cg6FNj53ER0tYcVdsWi0tQU0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDOWNLOAD\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EThe Klermont is a stock\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003Epaddle boat\u003C/span\u003E, which is as far as I am aware, the first stock\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003Epaddle boat\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0in KSP. It is powered by the same\u00A0DNBSD (scanner drive) which I used on my walker. This boat is mainly for looks, and not practicality. It is designed off 1800s-era Mississippi river boats, and has about 500 parts (yes i know, alot) There are two decks, the main cabin deck (lower one), and then the upper deck. Sadly Kerbals cannot walk around the boat while it is moving\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;line-height:28.8px;\u0022\u003EThe forward propulsion is being done by the paddle wheels (not\u00A0hidden\u00A0engines) and they are\u00A0powered by a scanner drive. Because of this, it\u00A0is slow. The top speed is ~3.4 m/s, however it can go on\u00A0infinitely. The only fuel drain is by a Juno, which provides the completely\u00A0aesthetic smoke. The paddle wheels work just like in real life, with much greater drag in the water, than out. Being powered by a\u00A0scanner\u00A0drive should mean that this boat even works on Eve, however I have not tested it.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EThe setup of the boat is quite simple. First get it into the water (I used vessel mover, but hyper edit or even building an under\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;line-height:28.8px;\u0022\u003Ecarriage\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0works too) then hit space twice. After the paddle wheel is decoupled, the engine is toggled on and off with the 1 action group. The smoke is just the throttle, and the lights are the lights button. There are hidden reaction wheels inside the craft, so it is able to turn using those.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;line-height:28.8px;\u0022\u003EThe boat is a medium size, being 34m long and 7.5m \u00A0wide, however the part count is very high due to it\u0027s mechanical aspects as well as many aesthetic parts. I hope you all enjoy it, as it was one of the funnest things I have built in a while.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;line-height:28.8px;\u0022\u003ESpecial thanks to Tfin, who came up with the name\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/w8vNO/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-21T03:28:54Z\u0022 title=\u002201/21/2016 03:28  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 21, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bubbadevlin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-21T12:16:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m very impressed! Good job!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bubbadevlin","CreatedById":136524,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-22T02:19:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222372532\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130384\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453378585\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250750\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Azimech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, Azimech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m very impressed! Good job!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! \u00A0With how many likes this thing has gotten, i am honestly surprised that there are not more comments! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-22T02:22:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks fun! How reliable is the Scanner drive?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bubbadevlin","CreatedById":136524,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-22T02:27:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222373593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130384\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453429349\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Majorjim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks fun! How reliable is the Scanner drive?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow, lol, The scanner drive is actually VERY reliable. This is because A) I had it very reliable in my walker, and this mechanism is just about a copy and paste. B) The ocean is flat, there are no hills or changes in the torque requited\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-22T02:30:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222373602\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130384\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453429644\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022136524\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bubbadevlin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bubbadevlin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow, lol, The scanner drive is actually VERY reliable. This is because A) I had it very reliable in my walker, and this mechanism is just about a copy and paste. B) The ocean is flat, there are no hills or changes in the torque requited\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah I could see it working better in the water. I did see your walker drive fail a few times though. It\u0027s just the nature of the beast..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-22T02:31:00Z\u0022 title=\u002201/22/2016 02:31  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 22, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Majorjim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Castille7","CreatedById":101668,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-22T03:25:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally nice build, I like the creative idea about building this! really cool and nice details\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"selfish_meme","CreatedById":125899,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-22T04:21:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just had nothing to say, it was great I liked it, would not change it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bubbadevlin","CreatedById":136524,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-22T19:30:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222373719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130384\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453436466\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125899\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022selfish_meme\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, selfish_meme said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just had nothing to say, it was great I liked it, would not change it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not mean to seem like I was whining for comments, it was actually unusual for how few people did comment, compared to how many liked it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-22T19:30:54Z\u0022 title=\u002201/22/2016 07:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 22, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bubbadevlin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"selfish_meme","CreatedById":125899,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-22T21:27:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222374496\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130384\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453491039\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022136524\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bubbadevlin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Bubbadevlin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not mean to seem like I was whining for comments, it was actually unusual for how few people did comment, compared to how many liked it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust need some old timer gambling suits and walk some kerbals around the deck\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-22T21:36:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuddenly wondering how Valentina would look in these clothes:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://3.bp.blogspot.com/_CvDCiEFbNy8/SiBCTSSLcsI/AAAAAAAAJGc/HUV7FqHeB4M/s1600/b.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022b.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe I\u0027ve had too much wine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bubbadevlin","CreatedById":136524,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T00:46:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLittle bump\u00A0as this got featured in SCF!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-24T00:48:16Z\u0022 title=\u002201/24/2016 12:48  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bubbadevlin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}